description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Occupational Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bath and North East Somerset&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£13.83-£17.01 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Occupational Therapist looking to gain invaluable experience in a variety of departments around Bath and North East Somerset? Are you looking for flexible NHS bank opportunities to fit around your lifestyle?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bath and North East Somerset now have a unique opportunity for a passionate and enthusiastic Occupational Therapist to join our paramedic team, hospital ward team or our community team to expand your knowledge and skills in fast paced environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel Valued&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Bank Occupational Therapist,you’ll be working as part of the NHS system in Bath and North East Somerset (BANES).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as the attractive hourly rates of pay, you’ll benefit from:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in an environment focused on the highest clinical and quality standards with 91% of our services being rated overall good or outstanding by the CQC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours, allowing you to achieve the best work / life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to work in different areas and various different services to gain new knowledge and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to our Strive for Better networks, a national support and professional network made up of NHS professionals like you, giving you the chance to constantly develop industry-leading care and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free statutory and mandatory training, as well as access to a range of courses and e-learning to develop further skills, continuing your professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to our free well-being service available 24/7/365 online and by telephone including; counsellors, post trauma incident support, legal, debt and practical life management helpline, guided self-help, telephonic career coaching and monthly well-being newsletters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to information on permanent vacancies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel Proud&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In BANES you’ll join a team who are dynamic, forward thinking and always go the extra mile.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have Bank opportunities for experienced Occupational Therapists who have a minimum of 12 months post graduate experience in the following areas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reenablement Service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Hospital ( st Martins or Paulton)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Falls Car&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stroke and Neuro Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also benefit from having a Professional Lead for Occupational Therapy working locally and always on hand for guidance and assistance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel the Difference&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We partner with the NHS and Local Authorities to deliver services which make a positive difference to the people working in them and relying on them. We don’t run private clinics, and Richard Branson has confirmed that if and when we make a profit in the future, he’ll re-invest it back into those services. In fact, we’ve never made a profit from publicly funded services and Virgin Group has invested £60m of additional funding which has helped ensure we can deliver high quality, sustainable and modern services and support the communities we serve&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if this sounds appealing to you, why not get in touch with our Professional Lead for Occupational Therapy Mandy Mills on:Mandy.Miles@virgincare.co.uk or 07515191907 to discuss this opportunity in more detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Virgin Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re committed to equal opportunities and welcome a broad diversity of talent to apply. We reserve the right to cease any advertising prior to the published closing date for a role that receives a high number of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Virgin Care is committed to safeguarding and protecting the children and young people that we work with. As such, all posts are subject to a safer recruitment process, including the disclosure of criminal records and vetting checks. We ensure that we have a range of policies and procedures in place which promote safeguarding and safer working practice across our services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Disability Confident Committed company, we work in partnership with the Department of Work and Pensions (DWP) to provide facilities, work environment adjustments and technical solutions to make our business an inclusive place for all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Virgin Care Limited, its subsidiary companies and the Virgin Care LLPs are part of the Virgin Group and provide publicly funded health and social care services. If you would like to know a little more about how we use your information, please see our website’s privacy policy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
